"title": "4807: colours",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4807",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A wide range of colours are mentioned in Scripture, some being used symbolically.</p>\n<h2>Colours mentioned in Scripture</h2>\n<h3>White</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:12\">GEN 49:12</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:27\">2KI 5:27</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Blue</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:6\">EST 1:6</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:24\">EZK 27:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod26:1\">EXO 26:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:22\">EXO 39:22</a></p>\n<h3>Yellow</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev9:17\">REV 9:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev13:30\">LEV 13:30</a></p>\n<h3>Green</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:39\">MRK 6:39</a></strong> <em>An indication as to the season; the grass is green in Galilee in spring.</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:30\">GEN 1:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:2\">PSA 23:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:8\">JER 17:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:7\">REV 8:7</a></p>\n<h3>Red</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs3:22\">2KI 3:22</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:2\">MAT 16:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:30\">GEN 25:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod36:19\">EXO 36:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:3\">REV 12:3</a></p>\n<h3>Purple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:17\">MRK 15:17</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:13\">NUM 4:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:22\">PRO 31:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:7\">DAN 5:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:14\">ACT 16:14</a></p>\n<h3>Scarlet</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:18\">ISA 1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:28\">GEN 38:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:23\">EXO 35:23</a> <em>Purple, scarlet, crimson and red are closely related and sometimes interchangeable in Scripture</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:8\">NUM 4:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:3\">SNG 4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:28\">MAT 27:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:4\">REV 17:4</a></p>\n<h3>Crimson</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:1\">ISA 63:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:7\">2CH 2:7</a></p>\n<h3>Black</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song5:11\">SNG 5:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:12\">REV 6:12</a></p>\n<h3>The whole spectrum</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:28\">EZK 1:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:3\">REV 4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev10:1\">REV 10:1</a></p>\n<h2>Colours used symbolically</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:2\">REV 6:2</a></strong> <em>White here symbolises conquest</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:3\">REV 17:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:4\">REV 6:4</a> <em>bloodshed and war</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:8\">REV 6:8</a> <em>death</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:9\">REV 7:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:14\">REV 19:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:11\">REV 19:11</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:11\">REV 20:11</a> <em>holiness</em></p>",
